        <p>
          Mindful living is not a destination — it is a direction. Some days will feel clearer
          than others, and that is entirely normal. The goal is not perfection but consistency:
          returning, again and again, to the simple act of noticing where you are and how you
          feel right now.
        </p>
        <p>
          Start with a single habit this week. Keep it small enough that skipping it would
          feel strange. Over time, these small deposits compound — and the interest they pay
          is a calmer, more intentional life.
        </p>
